webpackJsonp([0xb19ab4ee9fdb],{483:function(t,e){t.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Magento 1 Frontend Bits",author:"Claire Parker-Jones"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/Claire/gatsby-blog/src/pages/cdata/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>In my opinion: no.</p>\n<p>But it depends.</p>\n<h2>What does CDATA do?</h2>\n<p>You may have found <code>CDATA</code> declarations in template files (filetype <code>.phtml</code>),</p>\n<p>CDATA marks the text inside as not being XML or HTML. It is ignored by the XML parser.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/#sec-cdata-sect">https://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/#sec-cdata-sect</a></p>\n<p><a href="https://magento.stackexchange.com/questions/164569/put-cdata-it-is-a-good-practice-or-not-necessarily-magento-1-9">https://magento.stackexchange.com/questions/164569/put-cdata-it-is-a-good-practice-or-not-necessarily-magento-1-9</a></p>\n<p>It’s for validating XHTML markup when JavaScript is inline in the template. It means the validator doesn’t fail and ignores anything between those tags.</p>\n<p>This shouldn’t matter if you’re using the latest html5 doctype.</p>\n<p><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/66837/when-is-a-cdata-section-necessary-within-a-script-tag?rq=1">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/66837/when-is-a-cdata-section-necessary-within-a-script-tag?rq=1</a></p>',frontmatter:{title:"Do you need CDATA in templates?",date:"February 20, 2018"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/cdata/",previous:{fields:{slug:"/atom-snippets/"},frontmatter:{title:"How to add snippets for templates in Atom"}},next:{fields:{slug:"/cms-cms/"},frontmatter:{title:"How to output a CMS block from another CMS block"}}}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---cdata-70fa2b3a2989f5c33782.js.map